      <akn:section eId="sec_22_3133">
        <akn:num>22-3133</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Stalking.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_22-3133_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>It is unlawful for a person to purposefully engage in a course of conduct directed at a specific individual:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_22-3133_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>This section does not apply to constitutionally protected activity.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_22-3133_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Where a single act is of a continuing nature, each 24-hour period constitutes a separate occasion.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_22-3133_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The conduct on each of the occasions need not be the same as it is on the others.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
